{"title_page": "Jo Firestone", "text_new": "{{short description|American comedian, writer, and actor}}\n{{infobox person\n|birth_name = Joanna Firestone\n|occupation = Actress, comedian, writer\n|known = Appearances on ''The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon''\n}}\n'''Joanna Firestone''' is an actress, comedian, and television writer.<ref>[http://www.phillymag.com/ticket/2017/07/10/interview-comedian-jo-firestone/ Rapa, Patrick, \"Interview: Comedian Jo Firestone,\"] ''PhillyMag.com'', July 10, 2017</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nJoanna Firestone was born in 1987 to [[American Jews|Jewish]] parents Fred and Marilyn Firestone.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sophomore |first1=Louisa Goldman |title=Clayton comic having too much pun in NYC |url=https://www.stljewishlight.com/special_sections/ohr_chadash/clayton-comic-having-too-much-pun-in-nyc/article_48d02ab4-dbd8-11e3-bcec-0019bb2963f4.html |website=St. Louis Jewish Light |accessdate=22 April 2020}}</ref> She has a brother, Ben Firestone, who works in commercial real estate. She grew up in [[Clayton, Missouri]], a suburb of [[St. Louis, Missouri|St. Louis]]. She graduated from [[Clayton High School (Missouri)|Clayton High School]] and later [[Wesleyan University]] in Connecticut, with a degree in theatre.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gillerman |first1=Margaret S. |title=Father-daughter duo from Clayton taking NY by puns |url=https://www.stltoday.com/news/local/metro/father-daughter-duo-from-clayton-taking-ny-by-puns/article_5d3e21b3-9cc2-5999-8bc9-784f522db481.html |accessdate=22 April 2020 |work=St. Louis Post-Dispatch |publisher=Ray Farris |date=19 Mar 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Television work==\n\nAs an actress, Firestone has appeared in the TV programs ''[[Search Party (TV series)|Search Party]]'', ''[[The Jim Gaffigan Show]]'', ''[[Broad City]]'', ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'', ''[[CollegeHumor#CH Originals|CollegeHumor Originals]]'', ''[[Boy Band (TV series)|Boy Band]]'', ''[[The Outs]]'', ''[[Night Train with Wyatt Cenac]]'', ''Animal Agent'', ''[[High Maintenance]]'', ''[[Jon Glaser Loves Gear]]'', ''Thanksgiving'', ''[[The Special Without Brett Davis]]'', ''[[Shrill (TV series)|Shrill]]'', and others.<ref name=IMDB>[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm6847304/ Jo Firestone credits at IMDB.com]</ref> She was consulting producer on 21 episodes of ''[[The Chris Gethard Show]]'' and performed in three episodes of the series.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4877562/fullcredits Full Cast & Crew of ''The Chris Gethard Show'' at IMDB.com]</ref>\n\nShe is currently{{when?|date=February 2020}} a writer for ''The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon'' and for ''The Special Without Brett Davis''. She has also performed on the ''Tonight Show'', portraying [[U.S. Department of Education|U.S. Education]] Secretary [[Betsy DeVos]],<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RCJDn-vkAi4 Jimmy Fallon interviews U.S. Education Secretary Betsy DeVos (portrayed by Firestone)] ''The Tonight Show'', February 10, 2017</ref> demonstrating products from the New York Toy Fair,<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2cCN41A5uKQ \"Toy Fair Demo with ''Tonight Show'' Writer Jo Firestone,\"] ''The Tonight Show'', Feb. 25, 2017</ref> and appearing in other sketches opposite host [[Jimmy Fallon]].<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IU79mpoWbh8 \"What to Buy with Jo Firestone: Barbarian Octopus Beanie\"], ''The Tonight Show'', Oct. 12, 2017.</ref>  She is also currently playing the character Sarah Conner, a band teacher, on ''[[Joe Pera Talks with You]]'', which airs during [[Adult Swim]] on [[Cartoon Network]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Adams|first=Erik|url=https://tv.avclub.com/joe-pera-talks-with-you-is-the-adult-swim-comedy-that-l-1827064842|title=''Joe Pera Talks with You'' is the Adult Swim comedy that'll restore your soul|website=[[The A.V. Club]]|date=June 23, 2018|accessdate=July 3, 2018}}</ref><ref name=IMDB /> The character's [[Sarah Connor (Terminator)|name]] is an homage to the ''[[Terminator (franchise)|Terminator]]'' movies; her character is a doomsday prepper on the show.<ref name=Digg>{{cite web|last=Olson|first=Matthew|url=http://digg.com/2018/joe-pera-talks-with-you-restorative-comedy|title=Joe Pera Will Cure What Ails You|work=[[Digg]]|date=June 29, 2018|accessdate=July 3, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Other media==\nFirestone is the host of the program ''Dr. Gameshow'', which originated on [[WFMU]] radio and is now{{when?|date=February 2020}} a [[podcast]] on the [[Maximum Fun]] network.<ref>[http://www.wfmu.org/playlists/GM ''Dr. Gameshow'' archives at WFMU.org]</ref><ref>[https://maximumfun.org/shows/dr-gameshow Dr. Gameshow on Maximum Fun]</ref> She and her father Fred Firestone created the game ''Punderdome: A Card Game for Pun Lovers'' (published by [[Random House]] subsidiary [[Clarkson Potter]], 2016).<ref>[https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/533671/punderdome-by-by-daughter-father-duo-jo-and-fred-firestone-creators-of-punderdome-3000/9781101905654/ ''Punderdome: A Card Game for Pun Lovers'' at PenguinRandomHouse.com]</ref>\n\nFirestone has performed [[stand-up comedy]] on [[Comedy Central]],<ref>[http://www.cc.com/episodes/hgsotu/comedy-central-stand-up-presents-jo-firestone-season-1-ep-108 ''Comedy Central Stand-Up Presents Jo Firestone''], Season 1 Ep 6, 9/30/2017</ref> at the [[UCB Theater]] in Manhattan, and around New York City.<ref>[https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/lists/10-comedians-you-need-to-know-right-now-w485574/jo-firestone-w485579 Love, Matthew, \"10 Comedians You Need to Know\"], ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', June 6, 2017</ref><ref>[http://splitsider.com/2017/09/talking-standup-alone-time-and-why-comedy-is-bullshit-with-jo-firestone/ Kozell, Isaac, \"Talking Standup, Alone Time, and Why Comedy Is Bullshit with Jo Firestone,\"] SplitSider.com, September 29, 2017</ref> About stand-up gigs in \"cellar clubs,\" Firestone explained, \"Doing comedy in New York, I\u2019ve been conditioned to thrive in basements. I\u2019m not ready to do a comedy show until I go down a flight of stairs.\"<ref>[http://www.brooklynvegan.com/jo-firestone-talks-new-comedy-lp-the-return-of-her-podcast-will-butler-more-in-bv-interview/ Gordon, Arielle, \"Jo Firestone talks new comedy LP, the return of her podcast, Will Butler & more in BV interview,\"] ''Brooklyn Vegan'', September 5, 2017</ref>\n\nWith [[Dylan Marron]], Firestone wrote, performed in, and directed ''Ridgefield Middle School Talent Nite,''<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://capslove.wordpress.com/2010/07/15/funny-times-at-ridgefield-middle-school/|title=Funny Times At Ridgefield Middle School|date=2010-07-15|work=C.A.P.S.Love.|access-date=2018-03-28|language=en-US}}</ref> which received a Capital Fringe Festival Director's Award in 2010.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/going-out-gurus/post/the-capital-fringe-festival-preview-what-to-see/2011/07/06/gIQAlVy80H_blog.html|title=The Capital Fringe Festival Preview: What to See|last=Ramanathan|first=Stephanie Merry and Lavanya|date=2011-07-06|website=Washington Post|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-28}}</ref>\n\nFirestone voice acts in ''[[The National Lampoon Radio Hour]]'' podcast.<ref>[https://www.vulture.com/2019/09/national-lampoon-radio-hour-podcast-cast-writers.html, \"The National Lampoon Radio Hour to Feature All Your Favorite Comedy Babies\"], September. 19, 2019</ref> She serves as the producer and senior writer along with [[Cole Escola]].<ref>[https://www.nationallampoon.com/podcasts/radio-hour/, \"Lampoon Radio Hour Home Page\"]</ref>\n\n{{cns|date=February 2020|She is currently{{when?|date=February 2020}} based in [[Brooklyn]].}}\n\nIn March 2020 Firestone went on failed comedian Mike Recine's podcast [[The Sitdown]].<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ulcd-Z0dBj4, \"The Sitdown\"]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.jofirestone.com}}\n* [https://aux.avclub.com/game-loving-comic-jo-firestone-plays-a-wild-card-to-mak-1798163650 \"Game-loving comic Jo Firestone plays a wild card to make Pick A Choice history\"]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Firestone, Jo}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:American stand-up comedians]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American television writers]]\n[[Category:American women television writers]]\n[[Category:Comedians from New York City]]\n[[Category:Radio personalities from New York City]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American comedian, writer, and actor}}\n{{infobox person\n|birth_name = Joanna Firestone\n|occupation = Actress, comedian, writer\n|known = Appearances on ''The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon''\n}}\n'''Joanna Firestone''' is an actress, comedian, and television writer.<ref>[http://www.phillymag.com/ticket/2017/07/10/interview-comedian-jo-firestone/ Rapa, Patrick, \"Interview: Comedian Jo Firestone,\"] ''PhillyMag.com'', July 10, 2017</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nJoanna Firestone was born in 1987 to [[American Jews|Jewish]] parents Fred and Marilyn Firestone.{{cite web |last1=Sophomore |first1=Louisa Goldman |title=Clayton comic having too much pun in NYC |url=https://www.stljewishlight.com/special_sections/ohr_chadash/clayton-comic-having-too-much-pun-in-nyc/article_48d02ab4-dbd8-11e3-bcec-0019bb2963f4.html |website=St. Louis Jewish Light |accessdate=22 April 2020}}</ref> She has a brother, Ben Firestone, who works in commercial real estate. She grew up in [[Clayton, Missouri]], a suburb of [[St. Louis, Missouri|St. Louis]]. She graduated from [[Clayton High School (Missouri)|Clayton High School]] and later [[Wesleyan University]] in Connecticut, with a degree in theatre.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gillerman |first1=Margaret S. |title=Father-daughter duo from Clayton taking NY by puns |url=https://www.stltoday.com/news/local/metro/father-daughter-duo-from-clayton-taking-ny-by-puns/article_5d3e21b3-9cc2-5999-8bc9-784f522db481.html |