which airs during [[Adult Swim]] on [[Cartoon Network]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Adams|first=Erik|url=https://tv.avclub.com/joe-pera-talks-with-you-is-the-adult-swim-comedy-that-l-1827064842|title=''Joe Pera Talks with You'' is the Adult Swim comedy that'll restore your soul|website=[[The A.V. Club]]|date=June 23, 2018|accessdate=July 3, 2018}}</ref><ref name=IMDB /> The character's [[Sarah Connor (Terminator)|name]] is an homage to the ''[[Terminator (franchise)|Terminator]]'' movies; her character is a doomsday prepper on the show.<ref name=Digg>{{cite web|last=Olson|first=Matthew|url=http://digg.com/2018/joe-pera-talks-with-you-restorative-comedy|title=Joe Pera Will Cure What Ails You|work=[[Digg]]|date=June 29, 2018|accessdate=July 3, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Other media==\nFirestone is the host of the program ''Dr. Gameshow'', which originated on [[WFMU]] radio and is now{{when?|date=February 2020}} a [[podcast]] on the [[Maximum Fun]] network.<ref>[http://www.wfmu.org/playlists/GM ''Dr. Gameshow'' archives at WFMU.org]</ref><ref>[https://maximumfun.org/shows/dr-gameshow Dr. Gameshow on Maximum Fun]</ref> She and her father Fred Firestone created the game ''Punderdome: A Card Game for Pun Lovers'' (published by [[Random House]] subsidiary [[Clarkson Potter]], 2016).<ref>[https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/533671/punderdome-by-by-daughter-father-duo-jo-and-fred-firestone-creators-of-punderdome-3000/9781101905654/ ''Punderdome: A Card Game for Pun Lovers'' at PenguinRandomHouse.com]</ref>\n\nFirestone has performed [[stand-up comedy]] on [[Comedy Central]],<ref>[http://www.cc.com/episodes/hgsotu/comedy-central-stand-up-presents-jo-firestone-season-1-ep-108 ''Comedy Central Stand-Up Presents Jo Firestone''], Season 1 Ep 6, 9/30/2017</ref> at the [[UCB Theater]] in Manhattan, and around New York City.<ref>[https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/lists/10-comedians-you-need-to-know-right-now-w485574/jo-firestone-w485579 Love, Matthew, \"10 Comedians You Need to Know\"], ''[